---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';
import { Card, CardHeader, CardTitle, CardDescription, CardContent } from '../../components/ui/card';
import { Button } from '../../components/ui/button';
import { Badge } from '../../components/ui/badge';
import { getBlogPost } from '../../lib/blog-posts';

// Export frontmatter for auto-discovery
export const frontmatter = {
  title: 'The Deep Work Protocol',
  description: "How I 10x'd my productivity in 90 days",
  author: 'Emma Thompson',
  date: '2025-01-18',
  topic: 'productivity' as const,
  tags: ['focus', 'deep work', 'time management', 'habits', 'performance'],
};

const post = getBlogPost('deep-work-guide')!;
---

<BlogPostLayout post={post}>
  <p class="text-lg">
    In an age of constant distractions and endless notifications, the ability to focus deeply on cognitively demanding tasks has become increasingly rare‚Äîand increasingly valuable. Deep work isn't just about productivity; it's about producing work that matters and developing skills that set you apart in the modern economy.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500/10 to-indigo-500/10 border-l-4 border-blue-500 rounded-r-lg p-8 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-3">What is Deep Work?</h3>
    <p class="text-lg mb-4">
      Professional activities performed in a state of distraction-free concentration that push your cognitive capabilities to their limit. These efforts create new value, improve your skill, and are hard to replicate.
    </p>
    <p class="text-muted-foreground italic">
      "The ability to perform deep work is becoming increasingly rare at exactly the same time it is becoming increasingly valuable in our economy."
      <span class="block mt-2 not-italic font-semibold">‚Äî Cal Newport, Deep Work</span>
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Why Deep Work Matters</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8">
    <Card client:load className="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary/5 to-purple-500/5">
      <CardHeader>
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-primary" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <CardTitle className="text-xl">Rapidly Learn Hard Things</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Technology evolves quickly. Deep work allows you to master complex skills and adapt to new tools faster than your competition.
        </p>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>

    <Card client:load className="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-500/5 to-blue-500/5">
      <CardHeader>
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-purple-500/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-purple-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9.663 17h4.673M12 3v1m6.364 1.636l-.707.707M21 12h-1M4 12H3m3.343-5.657l-.707-.707m2.828 9.9a5 5 0 117.072 0l-.548.547A3.374 3.374 0 0014 18.469V19a2 2 0 11-4 0v-.531c0-.895-.356-1.754-.988-2.386l-.548-.547z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <CardTitle className="text-xl">Produce at an Elite Level</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          High-quality work requires sustained attention. Deep work enables you to produce output that stands out and creates real value.
        </p>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>

    <Card client:load className="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-500/5 to-indigo-500/5">
      <CardHeader>
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-lg bg-blue-500/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
          <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-blue-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14.828 14.828a4 4 0 01-5.656 0M9 10h.01M15 10h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
          </svg>
        </div>
        <CardTitle className="text-xl">Experience True Satisfaction</CardTitle>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          Shallow work feels busy but hollow. Deep work provides genuine fulfillment from creating meaningful contributions.
        </p>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">The Four Deep Work Philosophies</h2>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Different approaches work for different people and professions. Choose the philosophy that fits your lifestyle and work requirements:
  </p>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <Card client:load className="border-l-4 border-l-red-500">
      <CardHeader>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
          <CardTitle className="text-2xl">Monastic</CardTitle>
          <Badge client:load variant="destructive">Maximum Isolation</Badge>
        </div>
        <CardDescription>Eliminate or radically minimize shallow obligations</CardDescription>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">
          Best for individuals who can build their professional success around a single, well-defined pursuit. Think authors, researchers, or solo entrepreneurs.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Example:</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Donald Knuth (computer scientist) doesn't use email and focuses exclusively on writing his seminal works on programming.
          </p>
        </div>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>

    <Card client:load className="border-l-4 border-l-orange-500">
      <CardHeader>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
          <CardTitle className="text-2xl">Bimodal</CardTitle>
          <Badge client:load variant="secondary">Scheduled Isolation</Badge>
        </div>
        <CardDescription>Divide time into deep and open periods</CardDescription>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">
          Dedicate clearly defined stretches to deep pursuits (minimum of one full day). The rest of your time is open to everything else.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Example:</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Carl Jung maintained his clinical practice in Zurich but would retreat to his secluded tower for extended periods of deep thinking and writing.
          </p>
        </div>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>

    <Card client:load className="border-l-4 border-l-primary">
      <CardHeader>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
          <CardTitle className="text-2xl">Rhythmic</CardTitle>
          <Badge client:load>Daily Consistency</Badge>
        </div>
        <CardDescription>Create a daily habit of deep work sessions</CardDescription>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">
          The easiest way to consistently start deep work sessions. Transform deep work into a simple habit by doing it at the same time every day.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Example:</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Jerry Seinfeld's famous "Don't Break the Chain" method: write jokes every single day, marking an X on the calendar for each day completed.
          </p>
        </div>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>

    <Card client:load className="border-l-4 border-l-green-500">
      <CardHeader>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
          <CardTitle className="text-2xl">Journalistic</CardTitle>
          <Badge client:load variant="outline">Opportunistic</Badge>
        </div>
        <CardDescription>Fit deep work wherever you can into your schedule</CardDescription>
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <p class="text-sm mb-4">
          For those who can quickly switch into deep work mode. Requires practice and is not recommended for deep work novices.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-muted rounded-lg p-4">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold mb-2">Example:</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">
            Walter Isaacson would write his books in any spare moment he found, whether in a hotel room or between meetings.
          </p>
        </div>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Practical Deep Work Rituals</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-2xl">‚è∞</span>
        When You'll Work
      </h3>
      <div class="bg-card border rounded-lg p-5">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Block specific hours in your calendar (e.g., 9am-12pm daily)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Protect this time as fiercely as you would an important meeting</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Schedule deep work during your peak cognitive hours</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-2xl">üìç</span>
        Where You'll Work
      </h3>
      <div class="bg-card border rounded-lg p-5">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Choose a specific location (e.g., library, home office, coffee shop)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Ensure it's free from distractions and interruptions</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Consider a "grand gesture" like booking a hotel room for major projects</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-2xl">üéØ</span>
        How You'll Work
      </h3>
      <div class="bg-card border rounded-lg p-5">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Define clear goals for each session (e.g., "write 1000 words")</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Create rules to maintain focus (internet off, phone in drawer)</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Track your productivity to maintain accountability</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="text-2xl">‚ö°</span>
        How You'll Support
      </h3>
      <div class="bg-card border rounded-lg p-5">
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-sm">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Start with coffee or a light snack to maintain energy</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Use background music or white noise if it helps you focus</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary">‚Ä¢</span>
            <span>Keep necessary materials organized and accessible</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">The 4 Disciplines of Execution</h2>

  <div class="space-y-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-card border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl flex-shrink-0">1</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Focus on the Wildly Important</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            Identify a small number of ambitious outcomes to pursue with your deep work hours. The more you try to do, the less you actually accomplish.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-semibold">Ask yourself: "What is the most important thing I could be working on right now?"</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-card border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl flex-shrink-0">2</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Act on Lead Measures</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            Track behaviors that will drive success on your lag measures. For deep work, the key lead measure is time spent in deep work.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-semibold">Example: "I will spend 4 hours per day in deep work" (lead) vs "I will finish my book" (lag)</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-card border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl flex-shrink-0">3</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Keep a Compelling Scoreboard</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            Make your progress visible. Use a physical or digital tracker to mark each deep work hour completed.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-semibold">Visual tracking creates motivation and accountability</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-card border rounded-lg p-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-primary text-primary-foreground flex items-center justify-center font-bold text-xl flex-shrink-0">4</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Create a Cadence of Accountability</h3>
          <p class="text-muted-foreground mb-3">
            Review your scoreboard regularly. Weekly reviews help you understand what worked, what didn't, and how to improve.
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-primary font-semibold">Schedule a weekly review every Friday to assess your deep work progress</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-red-500/10 border-l-4 border-red-500 rounded-r-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-red-500" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M18.364 18.364A9 9 0 005.636 5.636m12.728 12.728A9 9 0 015.636 5.636m12.728 12.728L5.636 5.636" />
      </svg>
      Enemies of Deep Work
    </h3>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Digital Distractions</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Social media and news sites</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Email and chat notifications</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Smartphone interruptions</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4 class="font-semibold mb-2">Organizational Pressure</h4>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <li>‚Ä¢ Excessive meetings</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Instant response culture</li>
          <li>‚Ä¢ Open office layouts</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mt-12 mb-6">Getting Started: Your 30-Day Challenge</h2>

  <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-primary/10 to-purple-500/10 rounded-lg p-8 my-8">
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <Badge client:load>Week 1</Badge>
        <p class="text-sm"><strong>Baseline:</strong> Track your current deep work hours without changing behavior. You'll likely be shocked at how little focused time you have.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <Badge client:load>Week 2</Badge>
        <p class="text-sm"><strong>Experiment:</strong> Try blocking 90-minute deep work sessions each morning. Start with just one per day.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <Badge client:load>Week 3</Badge>
        <p class="text-sm"><strong>Expand:</strong> Increase to two deep work sessions per day. Experiment with different times to find your peak focus hours.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <Badge client:load>Week 4</Badge>
        <p class="text-sm"><strong>Optimize:</strong> Refine your ritual based on what worked. Aim for 3-4 hours of deep work daily as your new baseline.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="text-lg my-8">
    Remember: Deep work is a skill that must be trained. Start small, be consistent, and gradually build your capacity for sustained focus. The results‚Äîboth in output quality and personal satisfaction‚Äîwill be transformative.
  </p>

  <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 mt-8">
    <Button client:load variant="default">Download Deep Work Tracker</Button>
    <Button client:load variant="outline">View Productivity Tools</Button>
    <Button client:load variant="secondary">Join Focus Community</Button>
  </div>

</BlogPostLayout>
